Another problem is that of dogs on the recreation ground and footpaths which besides being unpleasant is a danger to health from toxoplasmosis and parasitic diseases.
This survey was carried out in 1985 by Elizabeth Jeffries, Louise Grubb, Edna May, Maureen Hadlow, Eileen Lockley + members of the L'bourne Womens Institute,Ivor Wilkinson of Wickhambreux donated the slides and Dr. Keith Dimond of Littlebourne entered the data into the computer. EV'UOY03200258
